<emphasis id="B91CAB7DFFDDFFFA56F0F9AF289A2976" box="[181,466,1599,1632]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
Ce 
<taxonomicName id="4C680CECFFDDFFFA56ADF9AF289A2976" authorityName="Boulard" authorityYear="2005" box="[232,466,1599,1631]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Megapomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Megapomponia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
est proche de 
<taxonomicName id="4C680CECFFDDFFFA54EEF9AF2D222949" authority="(Distant, 1905)" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[683,1130,1598,1632]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Megapomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B91CAB7DFFDDFFFA54EEF9AF2A362949" box="[683,894,1598,1632]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">M. intermedia</emphasis>
(Distant, 1905)
</taxonomicName>
et s’en distingue par sa tête au postclypéus proéminent et au rostre fort long, la forme de sa collerette pronotale, sa maculature thoracique fortement prononcée et par son abdomen plus fin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
